---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout isApp={false} title="Terms of Service">
  <article class="policy-page">
    <header class="policy-header">
      <p class="policy-eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="policy-date">Last Revised: March, 2026</p>
    </header>

    <div class="policy-summary">
      <h2>In short (not a legal substitute)</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          Using Scroll Reader means you accept these Terms and our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </li>
        <li>
          You are responsible for ensuring you have the right to upload any document you add to the app.
        </li>
        <li>
          Cards are generated by AI and may contain errors. They are for personal learning only.
        </li>
        <li>
          Scroll Reader is currently free. Paid plans are coming — we'll give you notice before anything changes.
        </li>
        <li>
          If you delete your account, all your uploaded documents and generated cards are permanently deleted from our servers.
        </li>
        <li>
          We do not sell or share your data with third parties.
        </li>
        <li>
          We may suspend access in cases of misuse.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="policy-summary-note">
        This summary is for convenience only. The full Terms of Service below are the legally binding agreement.
      </p>
    </div>

      <section class="policySection">
        <p>
          These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of Scroll Reader, including the website at
          scrollreader.app and any associated services, features, or applications (together, the "Services").
          By using the Services, you agree to be bound by these Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using Scroll Reader, you accept and agree to these Terms and our
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>. If you do not agree, please do not use the Services.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">User-Uploaded Content</h2>
        <p>
          Scroll Reader allows you to upload documents such as EPUBs and PDFs for personal use. You are solely
          responsible for ensuring that any content you upload does not infringe the copyright or other intellectual
          property rights of any third party. By uploading a document, you represent that you have the legal right
          to do so — for example, that you own the document, have purchased a license to it, or that it is in the
          public domain.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not review uploaded documents for copyright compliance. If you are unsure whether you have the right
          to upload a particular file, do not upload it.
        </p>
        <p>
          You retain ownership of all content you upload. By uploading, you grant us a limited license to process
          your content solely for the purpose of generating cards and operating the Services on your behalf.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">AI-Generated Content</h2>
        <p>
          Cards displayed in your feed are generated by large language models (currently Google Gemini). While we
          aim for quality and accuracy, AI-generated content may contain errors, omissions, or misrepresentations.
          All cards are for personal learning and informational purposes only. Do not rely on them as authoritative
          sources for academic, professional, medical, legal, or financial decisions.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">User Data and Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          We collect personal information you provide when creating an account, such as your name and email address.
          Please refer to our <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a> for details on how we collect, use, and protect
          your data. We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties.
        </p>
        <p>
          We use cookies and analytics to understand how the service is used and to improve it. You can manage
          cookie preferences through your browser settings.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Account Deletion and Data Retention</h2>
        <p>
          You may delete your account at any time from your account settings or by contacting us at
          <a href="mailto:contact@scrollreader.app">contact@scrollreader.app</a>. Upon deletion, all uploaded
          documents and AI-generated cards associated with your account will be permanently removed from our
          servers. This action is irreversible.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Pricing and Payments</h2>
        <p>
            Scroll Reader is currently free to use. Paid plans are planned for the future. We will notify registered
            users before introducing any charges. All payments, when introduced, will be handled by
            <a href="https://dodopayments.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Dodo Payments</a> — we do not store
            your payment card details.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Prohibited Activities</h2>
        <p>
          You agree not to use the Services to upload content that you do not have the right to use, to attempt
          to circumvent any technical limitations of the service, to engage in any activity that interferes with
          or disrupts the Services, or to use the Services for any unlawful purpose.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Termination of Service</h2>
        <p>
          We reserve the right to suspend or terminate access to the Services at our discretion, including in
          cases of misuse or violation of these Terms. You may terminate your account at any time by contacting
          us at <a href="mailto:contact@scrollreader.app">contact@scrollreader.app</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Termination of your account does not affect any obligations that arose under these Terms prior to
          termination.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          The Services are provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any kind, express or implied.
          We do not warrant that the Services will be uninterrupted, error-free, or that any content — including
          AI-generated cards — will be accurate or complete. Your use of the Services is at your own risk.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, Scroll Reader shall not be liable for any indirect,
          incidental, consequential, special, or exemplary damages arising from your use of the Services. This
          includes, without limitation, loss of data, loss of profits, or any harm resulting from reliance on
          AI-generated content.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Open Source</h2>
        <p>
          The Scroll Reader application is open source and licensed under the
          <a href="https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GNU Affero General Public License v3.0 (AGPL-3.0)</a>.
          The source code is available on GitHub. These Terms apply to the hosted service at scrollreader.app.
          If you self-host the software, the AGPL license governs your use of the code.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Governing Law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms are governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of India. Any disputes arising
          from these Terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the courts located in India.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Changes to These Terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms from time to time. If we make material changes, we will notify registered
          users by email or through the app before the changes take effect. Continued use of the Services after
          changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the revised Terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="policySection">
        <h2 data-order="2">Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have any questions about these Terms, please contact us at
          <a href="mailto:contact@scrollreader.app">contact@scrollreader.app</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  @reference "tailwindcss";

  /* ─── Page layout ─── */
  .policy-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 6rem 2rem 4rem;
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    color: var(--ed-on-surface);
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  /* ─── Header ─── */
  .policy-header {
    margin-bottom: 3.5rem;
  }

  .policy-eyebrow {
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: 0.25em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-header h1 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 4.5vw, 3rem);
    font-weight: 300;
    font-style: italic;
    line-height: 1.15;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .policy-date {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface-muted);
  }

  /* ─── Summary card ─── */
  .policy-summary {
    background: var(--ed-surface-high);
    border-radius: 0.375rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  .policy-summary h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-summary ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.6rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .policy-summary li {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface-dim);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
  }

  .policy-summary li::before {
    content: '\2013';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--ed-primary);
  }

  .policy-summary a {
    color: var(--ed-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--ed-outline);
  }

  .policy-summary-note {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface-muted);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* ─── Sections ─── */
  .policySection {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  .policySection h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: 1.35rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .policySection p {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface-dim);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .policySection ul {
    list-style: none;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 0;
  }

  .policySection li {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 300;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface-dim);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }

  .policySection li::before {
    content: '\2013';
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--ed-primary);
  }

  .policySection li > div {
    display: inline;
  }

  .policySection strong {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ed-on-surface);
  }

  .policySection a {
    color: var(--ed-primary);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
    text-decoration-color: var(--ed-outline);
    transition: text-decoration-color 0.2s;
  }

  .policySection a:hover {
    text-decoration-color: var(--ed-primary);
  }

  /* ─── Responsive ─── */
  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy-page {
      padding: 5rem 1.5rem 3rem;
    }
    .policy-summary {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>